## Performance Audit: Admin Assistant System

The file `admin/assistant/page.tsx` doesn't exist in this project. The admin assistant is built across these files:
- **`components/admin/AdminAssistantWorkspace.jsx`** (~1200 lines) — the main UI component
- **`pages/api/ai-chat.js`** — the API route (data fetching + LLM calls)
- **`lib/admin-assistant-direct-router.js`** — client-side routing
- **`lib/admin-assistant-surfaces.js`** — surface builder
- **`lib/admin-assistant-mutations.js`** — DB write operations

---

### Finding 1: Massive data fetch on every chat message (CRITICAL)

**File:** `pages/api/ai-chat.js:589-676`

`fetchDataContext()` fires **16 parallel Supabase queries** on every single POST to `/api/ai-chat`. This fetches:
- All crew workers, categories, jobs, superintendents, trucks
- 150 days of schedules, assignments, and rig details (lines 591-614: `historyStart` = -120 days, `historyEnd` = +30 days)
- All job positions, company contacts, contact submissions, job applications, social posts, brand voice profiles

Every time the user sends a message, the API re-fetches the entire operational dataset. **This is the single biggest bottleneck.**

The `modules` parameter on line 590 (`hasModule`) is defined but never used to filter — all 16 queries always run regardless.

### Finding 2: Full chat history sent with every request

**File:** `AdminAssistantWorkspace.jsx:461-479`

```js
const history = messages.map(({ role: messageRole, content }) => ({
  role: messageRole,
  content,
}));
```

The entire message history array is serialized and sent in the POST body on every message. As conversations grow, this payload balloons. There's no truncation or windowing — all messages accumulate unbounded in the `messages` state.

